<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-10-11T02:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-10-11T02:00:00-05:00" n="471" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d471">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">800.796/10–1144: Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Harriman</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                        </hi>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-10-11T10:00:00+03:00">October 11,
                                1944—10 a.m.</date>
                            <lb/> [Received 1:12 p.m.]</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>3890. Re Department’s circular, October 7, midnight.<note n="93" xml:id="d471fn93">Not printed; it contained detailed arrangements for
                            the Aviation Conference (800.796/10–744).</note> I have not yet had a
                        reply to my note of September 13 inviting the Soviet Government <pb facs="0567" n="557" xml:id="pg_557"/> to send a delegation to the
                        Conference on Postwar Civil Aviation.</p>
                    <p>I have written again requesting an early indication as to whether the Soviet
                        Government will find it possible to be represented at the Conference.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Harriman</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>